    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00/1926: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 23, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1575. For the Minister and Landis. War Department states that Commanding General,
                    Persian Gulf Command<note n="9" xml:id="d5fn9">Maj. Gen. Donald H.
                        Connolly.</note> and Commanding General, United States Army Forces in the
                    Middle East<note n="10" xml:id="d5fn10">Maj. Gen. Benjamin F. Giles.</note> have
                    been instructed to confer with appropriate State Department representatives and
                    to collaborate in implementing policy and procedure regarding Anglo-American
                    relations in Near and Middle East set forth in Department’s 1167, May 17, 10
                    p.m. Navy Department states its representatives throughout area have received
                    similar instructions.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Jidda, Jerusalem, Beirut, Tehran, Kabul, Aden, Addis Ababa. Separate
                    message sent to Baghdad.<note n="11" xml:id="d5fn11">Telegram No. 107 of the
                        same date.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Cairo. Repeated direct to London.<note n="12" xml:id="d5fn12">Repeated to
                        London as telegram No. 4950.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
